+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Thread Classification
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+## Changes Made
+
+- Updated `src/policy/approval_router.py` to normalize `approval_state` before calling `build_preview_payload(...)`.
+- Updated `src/policy/preview.py` so the preview-unavailable fallback payload preserves `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
+- Updated `tests/test_preview.py` with a regression case for `preview_enabled=False` plus `manual_review` normalization through `build_policy_preview(...)`.
+- Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback example reflects the corrected payload.
+
+## Behavioral Result
+
+`build_policy_preview(
+    request_id="req-214",
+    approval_state="manual_review",
+    preview_enabled=False,
+    actor="review-bot",
+)`
+
+now returns a fallback payload that keeps:
+
+- `approval_state="human_review_required"`
+- `requires_human_review=True`
+- `status="preview_unavailable"`
+
+## Validation
+
+- Ran `python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router`
+- Result: `Ran 5 tests ... OK`
