+`T-214-01`:
+Restored the fallback preview payload in `src/policy/preview.py` so `preview_enabled=False` now still includes `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`. The router now normalizes `manual_review` to `human_review_required` before building the payload.
+
+`T-214-02`:
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. No separate code change was needed because the same fallback payload fix resolves both threads.
+
+`T-214-03`:
+Marked obsolete. I did not apply the outdated suggestion to revive a legacy preview branch on the current code path.
+
+`T-214-04`:
+Added a regression test in `tests/test_preview.py` covering `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)` and asserting the fallback keeps `approval_state="human_review_required"` with `requires_human_review=True`.
+
+`T-214-05`:
+Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback example matches the corrected payload, including `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
